@Testnetters Earlier today we made **huge performance updates** to our Building the Parthenon Testnet site (https://testnet.movementlabs.xyz/) as well as to the Movement Aptos Testnet! :angry_moveus: 

- Now you should **see your up-to-the-moment completed Quests** (this should fix issues with not being able to see your quests or having old quest data) :peace: 

- Our testnet has passed the first stage and **the throttle has now been opened up more!** You should see fewer hanging or failed transactions on the Movement Aptos network:AAAAAAAA_1: (Some apps might experience some issues with the upgrade but this is temporary and part of the testnet process, so come back in a bit and try again as needed)

@Community Program @Study. Battle. Build. @Building The Parthenon @everyone Please note the changes in the announcement above ☝️

We're working to identify any problems with this transition to a more reliable way to keep track of Quests. Please let us know any issues in #❓┃testnet-feedback 

Remember, this update is to prepare us for some new features we're adding to the site next week... :poggers:
